  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Education Sector Response to COVID-19 Pandemic in Mongolia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The UN joint project aims to support the Government of Mongolia to implement the national COVID-19 preparedness and response plan by focusing on critical education and health services delivery. The emergency response UN project will support immediate education sector interventions to address the school closures. The UN will assist and support the Ministry of Education (MECSS) to ensure continuity and accessibility of quality basic on-line education services for children, adolescences, and youth, including those with disabilities and from ethnic minorities, which was interrupted by COVID-19 pandemic. The UN project will be jointly implemented by WHO, UNESCO, UNICEF and UNFPA.</narrative>
  </description>
